SIMPLE: moon-culminating
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Moon-culminating
<hw>Moon"-cul"mi*na`ting</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<def>Culminating, or coming to the meredian, at or about the same time
with the moon; -- said of a star or stars, esp. of certain stars
selected beforehand, and named in an ephemeris (as the Nautical
Almanac), as suitable to be observed in connection with the moon at
culmination, for determining terrestrial longitude.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mooned</ent>⟦br⟧
